text: Elizabeth Swann (later Elizabeth Turner) is a fictional character and the tritagonist of the Pirates of the Caribbean movie series. She appears in The Curse of the Black Pearl (2003) and three of its sequels, Dead Man's Chest (2006), At World's End (2007) and Dead Men Tell No Tales (2017). She is played by Keira Knightley. She is married to Will Turner. Elizabeth is the only child to Weatherby Swann, the love interest (later wife) to Will Turner, mother to Henry Turner and daughter-in-law to William “Bootstrap Bill” Turner. Swann becomes the Pirate king and captain of Singapore's pirate fleet in At World's End. ==References== Category:Pirates of the Caribbean characters Category:Fictional characters introduced in 2003
